_source.title: Sponsor a bed, change a life - $5,000
_source.description:
Each year, more than 45,000 sick children are admitted to The Royal Children’s Hospital (RCH). By sponsoring a hospital bed, you will help RCH doctors and nurses continue to provide world leading care to thousands of children throughout the year.  For a $5,000 nomination, sponsors may nominate to support bed/s in the following wards (subject to availability):
[list]
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/CockatooWard]Cockatoo Ward[/url][/b] supports children requiring ongoing surgical or neurological care
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/SugarGliderWard]Sugar Glider Ward[/url][/b] provides medical care to children with a range of conditions and illnesses
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/PlatypusWard]Platypus Ward[/url][/b] supports children requiring ongoing surgical care
[*]l[b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/KoalaWard]Koala Ward[/url][/b] cares for children with serious cardiac conditions
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/KookaburraWard]Kookaburra Ward[/url][/b] cares for patients battling childhood cancer
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/KelpieWard]Kelpie Ward[/url][/b] cares for our adolescent patients, our oncology patients and those requiring rehabilitative care
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/BanksiaWard]Banksia Ward[/url][/b] supports children and adolescents with mental health concerns
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/DolphinWard]Dolphin Ward[/url][/b] provides medical care for children requiring short hospital stays
[*][b][url=https://secure.rchfoundation.org.au/donate/PossumWard]Possum Ward[/url][/b] cares for children immediately after surgery
[/list]

_source.title: Donate to JOY this Radiothon
_source.description:
Financial support is extremely important to keep us On-Air broadcasting Out, Loud and Proud broadcasting for the LGBTI community.

[b]We rely on donations to provide these services in the community.[/b]
Our ability to continue to operate is due in large part to the generous support of individual donors who believe in what we do, as well as gifts from business supporters and corporations.  Thank you for considering our request.

If you make a donation of $10 (multiples of $10 count as multiple entries) before midnight on June 30 2017 you will go into the draw to win a cruise to New Caledonia!
[b]Every $2 you donate is tax deductible.[/b]

_source.title: Donate to QEI Foundation's Tax Appeal
_source.description:
[b]Did you know 80% of all blindness is avoidable or treatable?
Yet over 450,000 Australians are blind or vision impaired (Vision2020 Australia). [/b]

These statistics motivate the Queensland Eye Institute (QEI) Foundation each and every day to [b]SAVE SIGHT[/b].

We provide innovation and excellence in research, education and clinical care to reduce eye disease, improve eye health, and ultimately eliminate preventable blindness in the community. 

For as little as $2, you can make a positive impact as your tax-deductable donation can help QEI Foundation to [b]SAVE SIGHT. [/b]You may even be able to [b]DOUBLE YOUR IMPACT[/b] by asking your employer to match your donation!

With no government funding the Queensland Eye Institute’s survival relies solely on the generosity of donors, businesses and the community. 

Thank you for your support
